    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Land grants in colonial Latin America. These were given to subjects of the king to use territories for production and to regulate the rent of the territory’s inhabitants. This did not give the owner of the grant property rights to the land.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
